Tiinuy-an Falls is a three-tiered waterfalls with the highest cascade towering 55 meters. It is one of if not the widest waterfalls in the country at 95 meters width, aptly earning the title as the “Niagara Falls of the Philippines”.he name Tinuy-an comes from the Cebuano word Tinuyo-an, which translates as “an intentional act or performance to attain an objective or goal.” The name comes from a legend associated with the history of the waterfall.